@startuml
title Background Maintenance

actor Scheduler
participant "Memory Worker" as Worker
participant "Note Consolidator" as Consolidator
participant "Memory Repair Planner" as Repair
participant "Retention Worker" as Retention
database DB

Scheduler -> Worker: cron / debounce trigger

group Note consolidation
    Worker -> DB: SELECT mature notes
    DB --> Worker: note batch
    Worker -> Consolidator: consolidate(notes,\nrelated claims, tasks, profile)
    Consolidator --> Worker: claim/task/profile/episode ops\n+ note actions
    Worker -> DB: APPLY consolidation transaction
    Worker -> DB: INSERT MemoryRun
end

group Memory repair
    Worker -> DB: SELECT suspicious clusters\n(duplicates, conflicts, drift)
    DB --> Worker: suspicious items
    Worker -> Repair: plan_repair(items,\nsupporting evidence)
    Repair --> Worker: repair ops
    Worker -> DB: APPLY repair transaction
    Worker -> DB: INSERT MemoryRun
end

group Retention / forgetting
    Worker -> DB: SELECT retention candidates
    DB --> Worker: stale / low-use items
    Worker -> Retention: classify keep / warm / cold /\narchive / delete
    Retention --> Worker: retention ops
    Worker -> DB: APPLY retrieval_state changes\narchive / delete per policy
    Worker -> DB: INSERT MemoryRun
end

note over Worker, DB
Consolidation makes memory richer.
Repair keeps memory healthy.
Retention keeps retrieval bounded over time.
end note

@enduml
